# âš›ï¸ QuantumCrackSim: Grover-Based Password Search Simulation

QuantumCrackSim is a modular simulation framework that models password cracking logic using Groverâ€™s Algorithm over contextual dictionaries and hashcat-like masks. It is designed for experimentation within Azure Quantum environments, offering insight into quantum search acceleration over classical brute-force techniques.

---

## ğŸ¯ Objective

To evaluate the feasibility and performance of Grover's algorithm when applied to password search problems modeled from real-world dictionaries and structured character masks. The simulation highlights how quantum principles reduce search complexity from linear **O(N)** to quadratic **O(âˆšN)**.

